We may have had plenty of rain this past week but Rand Water is warning of water levels dropping sharply in reservoirs around Johannesburg. It seems there has been a significant increase in water demand. The problem worsened by load-shedding which hampers the pump stations. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - Residents of Tshwane and Johannesburg are being urged to use water sparingly. This is because Rand Water's distribution systems are under pressure, leading to low levels in reservoirs. Rand Water spokesperson Justice Mohale there's enough raw water, but purifying it is costly and time-consuming. READ: Rand Water warns of water problems across Joburg "Raw water has to be taken through rigorous purification processes and the cost thereof is very high," Mohale said. "That is why we always tell people to use water responsibly.